# Go Style

## Copyright Header

Every Go file starts with the copyright header before the package declaration:

```go
// Copyright (c) 2026 Nokia. All rights reserved.
```

## Implementation Strategy

Write all source files before running build or test commands. Plan the full implementation, write each file in dependency order, then compile and test once. No incremental compile-fix loops.

## Interfaces

Every boundary between a parent package and its internal sub-packages must be defined by an interface, even when only one implementation exists. Accept interfaces as parameters; return concrete structs. Keep interfaces small: one to three methods. Do not use `interface{}` or `any` as parameters, return types, or struct fields.

## Design Patterns

Use Strategy (not if/else ladders), Command (encapsulate actions), Facade (hide multi-step processes), Factory (`NewXxx()` constructors), Decorator (cross-cutting concerns), Builder (functional options for many optional fields), Adapter (wrap foreign APIs), Observer (channels for async notification).

## Error Handling

Guard clauses: check `err != nil`, return early. Wrap with context: `fmt.Errorf("doing X: %w", err)`. Never silently discard errors except best-effort cleanup (comment required). Return errors for runtime conditions; panic only for programming contract violations. Never panic on I/O or user input.

## Naming

- Exported: PascalCase. Unexported: camelCase. CLI flags: kebab-case.
- Binary constants: `binXxx` prefix. Factories: `NewXxx()`.
- Receivers: one/two-letter abbreviation (e.g., `o` for Orchestrator). Never `self`/`this`. Consistent across all methods of a type.
- Pointer receivers for stateful/large types; value receivers for small immutable types. Never mix on one type.

## File & Package Organization

- `cmd/`: entry points. `internal/`: private implementation. `pkg/`: public API. `tests/`: integration. `magefiles/`: build tooling.
- Name files by concern, not kind. No `types.go`, `helpers.go`, `utils.go`.
- Order: constants/types, constructors, exported symbols, unexported helpers, `main()`.
- Imports in three groups separated by blank lines: stdlib, external, internal.

## Functions & Structs

- Each struct: one concept. Each function: one thing.
- More than three parameters: group into a config struct.
- Functions max 200 lines; split at natural seams. Hard limit 40 LOC per constitution E8.
- Files max 500 LOC per constitution E9.
- DRY threshold: two occurrences, then extract.

## Testing

Table-driven tests with named rows and `t.Run`. Call `t.Parallel()` first in every safe test (never with `os.Chdir()` or global state mutation). Call `t.Helper()` first in every helper. Use `TestMain` for one-time package setup. Tests cover contracts, not implementation.

## Constants

No magic strings. Centralize binary names, paths, URLs as named constants. Use typed `iota` enums for fixed value sets.

## Misc

- `context.Context` as first parameter for I/O functions. Protect mutable global state with `sync.Mutex`.
- Avoid `init()` except for driver registration or infallible lookup tables.
- All config flows through `configuration.yaml` / Viper. No `os.Getenv()` for app config.
- Godoc comment on every exported symbol, starting with the symbol name.
